A man has died following a gang brawl in Newlands East, Durban, on Sunday. He was injured while a group of people were attacking each other. In a video doing the rounds on social media, residents can be heard screaming as someone takes out a gun and starts firing shots. "It is alleged that it was an altercation between two rivals," said police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gala. Gwala confirmed to News24 that a man had been injured and had later succumbed to his wounds. Police are now investigating a case of murder.